          <msContents>
            <summary>Selections from Baudhāyana's Prayogasāra and is a collection of rules and regulations (dharma or Hindu law) containing Vedic rites for use by Hotṛ priests; specifically related to the Pauṇḍarīka ceremony which lasts 11 days; this rite is focused on the elixir soma, a mind-altering, ancient drug.</summary>
